cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.Distributed, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a new paradigm for permissioned blockchains to support distributed applications that execute concurrently. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses confidentiality issues in existing blockchains and proposes a new permissioned blockchain system. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of existing blockchains and proposes a new system to address these limitations. 
- cs.Distributed is relevant as the paper focuses on designing a permissioned blockchain system for distributed applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as the paper proposes a new paradigm for permissioned blockchains and presents a new system designed in this paradigm.
